BLOSUM(LOCAL)                                                    BLOSUM(LOCAL)



NNAAMMEE
       BLOSUM - Construct blosum scoring matrix from sequence block file

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       BBLLOOSSUUMM [[ooppttiioonnss]] _-_c _-_s _-_o _-_h

AAVVAAIILLAABBIILLIITTYY
       Unix

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       BLOSUM  calculates BLOcks of amino acid SUbstitution Matrix for protein
       block file from convergence level 1  to  100.  It  uses  the  algorithm
       advanced  by  STEVEN  HENIKOFF  AND JORJA G. HENIKOFF Proc. Natl. Acad.
       Sci. USA Vol. 89, pp. 10915-10919.

UUSSAAGGEE
       BLOSUM uses "blocks.dat" located in working  dir  by  default.  Use  -c
       option to specify custom block file. Just type "BLOSUM" (or "./BLOSUM")
       in the command line will trigger the program to use "blocks.dat"  file.
       By   default,  it  will  output  two  files  "RltvFreq.txt"  and  "BLO‚Äê
       SUM_score.txt". Use -s to suppress the output of RltvFreq.txt,  and  -o
       "xxx" to customize the name of BLOSUM_score.txt.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       -c  *.*  use  customized block file. The script is defaulted to use the
       blocks.dat comes with the program

       -s suppress relative frequency output.

       -o *.* customize the output name of scoring matrix

       -h open this help file

AAUUTTHHOORR
       Xiaoyang Ruan




